SIMPLE: similar
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Similar
<hw>Sim"i*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>similaire</ets>, fr. L. <ets>similis</ets> like, similar. See
<er>Same</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and cf. <er>Simulate</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Exactly corresponding; resembling in all respects;
precisely like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nearly corresponding; resembling in many respects;
somewhat like; having a general likeness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Homogenous; uniform.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Similar figures</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>figures
which differ from each other only in magnitude, being made up of the
same number of like parts similarly situated.</cd> -- <col><b>Similar
rectilineal figures</b></col>, <cd>such as have their several angles
respectively equal, each to each, and their sides about the equal angles
proportional.</cd> -- <col><b>Similar solids</b></col>, <cd>such as are
contained by the same number of similar planes, similarly situated, and
having like inclination to one another.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Similar</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Similar
<hw>Sim"i*lar</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is similar to, or
resembles, something else, as in quality, form, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Similarity</ent>⟦br⟧
